1
00:00:10,062 --> 00:00:13,062
[somber music playing]

2
00:00:15,479 --> 00:00:18,062
[reporter 1] Around 20 shell casings
were found at the scene.

3
00:00:18,146 --> 00:00:21,312
[reporter 2] A little before 2:00 a.m.
in Vauclin, gunfire reportedly broke out

4
00:00:21,396 --> 00:00:24,687
inside a nightclub according to
the first findings of the investigation.

5
00:00:24,771 --> 00:00:27,146
[reporter 1] And a young mother
in critical condition.

6
00:00:27,229 --> 00:00:30,562
This is the toll of a shooting that
took place at a local club last night.

7
00:00:30,646 --> 00:00:34,562
[reporter 3] This is already the second
shooting inside a nightclub this year.

8
00:00:34,646 --> 00:00:38,396
[reporter 2] …in a nightclub last night
which cost the life of a young man,

9
00:00:38,479 --> 00:00:41,312
while a young woman is still hospitalized
in serious condition.

10
00:00:41,396 --> 00:00:44,271
[reporter 4] …faced with the
growing violence and recent shootings,

11
00:00:44,354 --> 00:00:48,354
as a result of the explosion
in drug trafficking in Martinique.

12
00:00:48,437 --> 00:00:51,437
[somber music continues]

13
00:00:53,937 --> 00:00:57,104
[reporter 4] Martinique witnessed
its 25th murder by firearm this year…

14
00:00:57,187 --> 00:00:59,062
[reporter 5] Perpetrators
are getting younger.

15
00:00:59,146 --> 00:01:02,271
According to a police source,
80% of armed people in Martinique

16
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:05,104
are between 14 and 25 years old.

17
00:01:05,187 --> 00:01:08,521
- [helicopter whirring]
- [somber music continues]

18
00:01:14,646 --> 00:01:16,646
- [music fades]
- [door opens]

19
00:01:17,729 --> 00:01:19,354
[man] Gentlemen, please come in.

20
00:01:28,312 --> 00:01:31,812
We called you in because these men
would like to ask you a few questions.

21
00:01:32,312 --> 00:01:34,812
[officer] We're here
as a part of an investigation.

22
00:01:34,896 --> 00:01:37,354
We're looking for your brother.
We'd like to speak with him.

23
00:01:37,437 --> 00:01:38,687
Which one?

24
00:01:39,437 --> 00:01:40,479
Kingsley.

25
00:01:40,979 --> 00:01:42,646
We're searching for Kingsley.

26
00:01:42,729 --> 00:01:44,146
For what purpose?

27
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:46,437
[officer] We just want
to ask him some questions.

28
00:01:46,521 --> 00:01:48,354
We went to your house and saw Marvin.

29
00:01:48,437 --> 00:01:50,521
He knows nothing, of course.

30
00:01:51,229 --> 00:01:52,604
Questions about what?

31
00:01:52,687 --> 00:01:54,854
[officer] It's important.
That's all we can say.

32
00:01:54,937 --> 00:01:57,062
Do you know where he is or not?

33
00:01:57,146 --> 00:01:58,979
BORDER POLICE

34
00:01:59,562 --> 00:02:00,979
For now, he hasn't done anything.

35
00:02:01,062 --> 00:02:03,229
If you see him,
you can pass along the message.

36
00:02:03,312 --> 00:02:06,021
We'd like to talk to him.
He knows the victim very well.

37
00:02:06,104 --> 00:02:08,104
He's clashed with him before.

38
00:02:09,521 --> 00:02:10,896
No way, that's impossible.

39
00:02:10,979 --> 00:02:12,021
He wouldn't.

40
00:02:13,896 --> 00:02:15,854
What were you doing on the mainland?

41
00:02:16,646 --> 00:02:18,437
I was visiting my boyfriend.

42
00:02:19,229 --> 00:02:22,937
- So when did you last see your brother?
- At the appointment with the judge.

43
00:02:23,021 --> 00:02:25,437
When she gave my siblings to a pedophile.

44
00:02:25,521 --> 00:02:28,646
You know, the moment
when y'all forgot to do your own jobs.

45
00:02:28,729 --> 00:02:30,396
- Young lady--
- Don't "young lady" me!

46
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:32,187
Ambre, listen, please.

47
00:02:32,271 --> 00:02:34,937
[officer] Okay, calm down.
We just want to speak with him.

48
00:02:35,021 --> 00:02:37,729
- He never calls you?
- We sometimes message each other.

49
00:02:37,812 --> 00:02:39,562
He's an adult. He does what he wants.

50
00:02:39,646 --> 00:02:42,437
Is he living alone?
He's not living with you?

51
00:02:43,146 --> 00:02:45,146
We're all split up since Mom's passing.

52
00:02:45,229 --> 00:02:46,937
Us two board at the school.

53
00:02:47,021 --> 00:02:50,229
[officer] But you never see your brother?
You don't know what he's up to?

54
00:02:50,729 --> 00:02:53,604
We're no longer a family! That's a fact!

55
00:02:54,812 --> 00:02:57,812
["Reality" by Lov'Nee playing]

56
00:03:09,646 --> 00:03:13,104
MY BROTHER DID SOMETHING STUPID.

57
00:03:14,854 --> 00:03:20,187
I'M SWITCHING PHONES

58
00:03:20,271 --> 00:03:23,271
- [school bell ringing]
- [kids chatting indistinctly]

59
00:03:23,354 --> 00:03:26,354
[pensive rap song continues playing]

60
00:03:30,437 --> 00:03:31,687
So now I'm a liar.

61
00:03:31,771 --> 00:03:34,687
My baby brother's a dealer.
My older brother's an assassin.

62
00:03:34,771 --> 00:03:36,396
I'm very proud, can't you tell?

63
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,979
We can't be sure it's him.

64
00:03:39,729 --> 00:03:43,062
Stop taking me for a fool
like you do with everyone else.

65
00:03:43,146 --> 00:03:44,604
[Kylian exhales]

66
00:04:05,312 --> 00:04:06,312
So?

67
00:04:07,062 --> 00:04:08,687
No one knows where he is.

68
00:04:09,312 --> 00:04:10,937
We'll find him soon enough.

69
00:04:12,062 --> 00:04:13,312
And do what after?

70
00:04:14,229 --> 00:04:16,729
He's going to get busted, bro.
What if he rats us out?

71
00:04:16,812 --> 00:04:17,937
He would never do that.

72
00:04:18,021 --> 00:04:19,979
And what if he does?

73
00:04:21,687 --> 00:04:25,271
What do you want me to do?
For real, tell me. I'm interested.

74
00:04:27,479 --> 00:04:29,646
Nothing. It's not your problem anymore.

75
00:04:29,729 --> 00:04:30,729
That true?

76
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,604
Whose problem is it?

77
00:04:36,146 --> 00:04:39,146
- [tense music playing]
- [Fatso] What the fuck is he here for?

78
00:04:41,437 --> 00:04:43,229
[Kylian] Was he following me?

79
00:04:53,937 --> 00:04:54,937
[Marco] Drive.

80
00:04:58,104 --> 00:04:59,104
Drive where?

81
00:04:59,604 --> 00:05:02,562
- You'll see. Drive.
- This isn't how you treat a partner.

82
00:05:02,646 --> 00:05:05,062
You're a crappy-ass partner. Let's go.

83
00:05:06,771 --> 00:05:07,771
[car starting]

84
00:05:07,854 --> 00:05:10,854
[tense music playing]

85
00:05:29,896 --> 00:05:32,937
NIGHT OF TERROR IN FORT-DE-FRANCE
SHOOTING RAISES CONCERNS OF DRUG VIOLENCE

86
00:05:33,021 --> 00:05:34,937
[Marco] Is our merchandise safe?

87
00:05:36,104 --> 00:05:37,312
What do you think?

88
00:05:37,396 --> 00:05:40,271
We're gonna lose them
because of your asshole brother.

89
00:05:40,771 --> 00:05:42,354
Where you get that bullshit?

90
00:05:43,771 --> 00:05:47,146
Your brother's gonna get arrested.
You'll be arrested after that.

91
00:05:47,729 --> 00:05:49,312
Someone will talk.

92
00:05:49,396 --> 00:05:50,729
Cops will be everywhere.

93
00:05:51,937 --> 00:05:53,687
They'll set an example.

94
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:56,521
[angrily] Do I look like an example?

95
00:05:56,604 --> 00:05:59,062
With millions
of our money floating around?

96
00:06:00,354 --> 00:06:03,187
- Didn't I tell you to not make any noise?
- [knife flicks]

97
00:06:05,229 --> 00:06:09,062
We don't do business
with someone who attracts so much trouble.

98
00:06:14,479 --> 00:06:16,187
You know exactly what needs to happen.

99
00:06:16,271 --> 00:06:19,396
[somber music playing]

100
00:06:21,312 --> 00:06:22,312
No.

101
00:06:23,521 --> 00:06:25,812
You prefer that we do this to Léo?

102
00:06:25,896 --> 00:06:28,521
You'll receive
small pieces of him each day.

103
00:06:29,854 --> 00:06:32,396
He's gonna be going far away
and never coming back.

104
00:06:32,479 --> 00:06:33,604
He won't be a problem.

105
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:38,104
My boss always says…

106
00:06:39,271 --> 00:06:42,771
only death is guaranteed, understand?

107
00:06:43,646 --> 00:06:47,312
[in Spanish] "Only death… is guaranteed."

108
00:06:49,521 --> 00:06:51,771
[somber music continues]

109
00:07:20,604 --> 00:07:22,604
- [music fades]
- [insects chirping softly]

110
00:07:25,062 --> 00:07:27,062
[knock on door]

111
00:07:30,812 --> 00:07:31,812
[in English] Yes?

112
00:07:31,896 --> 00:07:34,187
- [woman] Open up.
- Who is it?

113
00:07:34,271 --> 00:07:36,271
[woman] What are you afraid of? Open up.

114
00:08:03,104 --> 00:08:04,229
What do you want?

115
00:08:04,312 --> 00:08:06,021
Don't play dumb with me.

116
00:08:10,437 --> 00:08:12,271
- [man] He's not here.
- Where'd he go?

117
00:08:13,021 --> 00:08:14,021
Who?

118
00:08:15,396 --> 00:08:16,562
- [blow lands]
- Ahh!

119
00:08:16,646 --> 00:08:17,854
[loudly] Where'd he go?

120
00:08:19,604 --> 00:08:20,604
I don't know.

121
00:08:27,229 --> 00:08:30,229
- [blow landing]
- [pensive music playing]

122
00:08:48,021 --> 00:08:51,021
[darkly expectant music playing]

123
00:08:58,812 --> 00:09:00,812
[music fades]

124
00:09:02,312 --> 00:09:03,312
[whistles softly]

125
00:09:08,187 --> 00:09:09,187
[whistles]

126
00:09:17,896 --> 00:09:20,687
- [Mathis] King!
- ["Ti Milo" by Lé Will & Deuspi playing]

127
00:09:24,937 --> 00:09:27,021
- [Thaïs] King!
- [Kingsley chuckling]

128
00:09:27,604 --> 00:09:30,354
- [Thaïs] Where were you?
- Not far, alligators.

129
00:09:30,854 --> 00:09:33,187
- [Nolan] You're the alligator.
- No, I'm not.

130
00:09:35,312 --> 00:09:38,312
- [upbeat song continues in background]
- [King chuckles]

131
00:09:41,187 --> 00:09:43,271
There's a present for y'all in there.

132
00:09:43,354 --> 00:09:44,771
[bag rustling]

133
00:09:46,604 --> 00:09:48,271
Oh yum, candy!

134
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:49,354
[Mathis] Hey!

135
00:09:49,979 --> 00:09:52,062
Will you tell us a story?

136
00:09:52,146 --> 00:09:54,229
Mmm, which one?

137
00:09:54,312 --> 00:09:57,271
The story of the lions and the beasts.

138
00:09:57,354 --> 00:09:58,771
Hmm, okay.

139
00:09:58,854 --> 00:10:01,729
We've got to be super quiet.
Whisper like mice.

140
00:10:02,271 --> 00:10:04,312
- All set?
- [kids] All set.

141
00:10:05,687 --> 00:10:06,771
King, you're here?

142
00:10:07,562 --> 00:10:08,812
No, I'm not here.

143
00:10:09,312 --> 00:10:10,604
Come.

144
00:10:13,771 --> 00:10:15,062
[Kingsley] Mmm.

145
00:10:17,687 --> 00:10:20,354
- And Léo, where's he?
- On a language trip.

146
00:10:21,354 --> 00:10:22,521
Oh! Where to?

147
00:10:27,562 --> 00:10:28,854
Okay, alligators,

148
00:10:28,937 --> 00:10:31,729
Today, I'm going to tell you
the secret story of the phantom resort.

149
00:10:31,812 --> 00:10:35,687
Because, as you know, phantoms also
have the right to have vacation.

150
00:10:37,146 --> 00:10:41,021
So it all begins in a very large mansion…

151
00:10:41,104 --> 00:10:43,187
that's full of little cute phantoms.

152
00:10:44,187 --> 00:10:46,562
But there is one
that is different among them.

153
00:10:49,937 --> 00:10:55,479
[girl in Spanish]
One, two, three, four, five…

154
00:10:55,562 --> 00:11:01,771
six, seven, eight, nine, ten…

155
00:11:02,271 --> 00:11:08,312
eleven, twelve,
thirteen, fourteen, fifteen…

156
00:11:08,396 --> 00:11:14,479
sixteen, seventeen,
eighteen, nineteen, twenty!

157
00:11:14,562 --> 00:11:15,562
Here I come!

158
00:11:37,687 --> 00:11:39,021
This is the Art.

159
00:11:39,104 --> 00:11:40,604
I don't understand.

160
00:11:40,687 --> 00:11:44,979
In this house, the places,
the shadows are your friends.

161
00:11:45,646 --> 00:11:48,854
You need to observe,
remember, and blend in.

162
00:11:50,896 --> 00:11:52,271
This is the Art.

163
00:12:02,187 --> 00:12:03,521
[in English] Crazy!

164
00:12:03,604 --> 00:12:05,604
[in Spanish] What are you doing, Diablo?

165
00:12:05,687 --> 00:12:06,937
Nothing, boss.

166
00:12:13,521 --> 00:12:15,354
Are you getting attached to the kid?

167
00:12:18,812 --> 00:12:20,396
You'll have to kill him, you know.

168
00:12:21,146 --> 00:12:22,146
Yes, boss.

169
00:12:23,687 --> 00:12:25,521
And he'll need to scream a bit…

170
00:12:26,354 --> 00:12:28,271
so that his brother can hear him.

171
00:12:32,396 --> 00:12:33,396
Good.

172
00:12:36,479 --> 00:12:40,229
[in English] And then the baby phantom
returned home excited,

173
00:12:40,312 --> 00:12:42,187
because he met a little girl phantom,

174
00:12:42,271 --> 00:12:46,021
so now they talk nonstop,
messaging all the time on WhooWhoo,

175
00:12:46,104 --> 00:12:47,896
the app made for phantoms.

176
00:12:48,854 --> 00:12:51,896
All right, everyone to bed.

177
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:53,062
[kid grunts softly]

178
00:13:11,604 --> 00:13:12,604
SherKhan?

179
00:13:13,104 --> 00:13:14,229
[Kingsley] Hmm?

180
00:13:14,312 --> 00:13:15,312
He was murdered.

181
00:13:15,396 --> 00:13:16,937
No way!

182
00:13:17,729 --> 00:13:18,729
You didn't know?

183
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:27,354
And his cousin, Vincez?

184
00:13:28,062 --> 00:13:30,229
If SherKhan is dead, he's good.

185
00:13:37,854 --> 00:13:40,854
[dark music playing]

186
00:14:16,479 --> 00:14:17,646
[exhales]

187
00:14:19,687 --> 00:14:22,021
I'm sorry. I can't trust anybody.

188
00:14:22,979 --> 00:14:25,646
I didn't mean to kill him.
He tried to set me up, bro.

189
00:14:25,729 --> 00:14:26,896
Is that the gun?

190
00:14:27,896 --> 00:14:30,521
- [Kingsley] Yeah.
- You can't keep it. Let me take it.

191
00:14:30,604 --> 00:14:31,729
No.

192
00:14:34,437 --> 00:14:35,562
Does the family know?

193
00:14:38,312 --> 00:14:39,312
What do we do now?

194
00:14:40,312 --> 00:14:41,354
I don't know.

195
00:14:41,437 --> 00:14:42,937
Police are looking for you.

196
00:14:43,437 --> 00:14:44,896
I've gotta go, brother.

197
00:14:45,937 --> 00:14:47,687
You fucked everything up.

198
00:14:47,771 --> 00:14:49,854
- What did I fuck up, exactly?
- Everything!

199
00:14:50,604 --> 00:14:52,104
I had a plan with no flaws.

200
00:14:52,187 --> 00:14:53,812
And it's over because of you.

201
00:14:54,479 --> 00:14:55,812
That's your problem, man.

202
00:14:55,896 --> 00:14:57,646
It's also Léo's problem.

203
00:14:59,896 --> 00:15:00,896
What do you mean?

204
00:15:01,562 --> 00:15:03,687
Do you know how much money one ton is?

205
00:15:04,854 --> 00:15:06,729
A total of nearly ten million.

206
00:15:07,312 --> 00:15:09,062
And I had one ton, King.

207
00:15:09,146 --> 00:15:11,562
They should've been shipped,
but they can't move.

208
00:15:12,271 --> 00:15:15,479
You know what they want to make me do?
Kill your ass.

209
00:15:20,604 --> 00:15:21,979
You need to disappear.

210
00:15:22,729 --> 00:15:25,396
You've gotta move on… for a long time.

211
00:15:25,479 --> 00:15:28,021
It's the only way to save yourself
and us too.

212
00:15:28,521 --> 00:15:30,312
What does that have to do with Léo?

213
00:15:33,354 --> 00:15:34,896
They took him as guarantee.

214
00:15:36,104 --> 00:15:38,062
I don't know
what they'll do to him if you stay.

215
00:15:38,146 --> 00:15:40,729
Wait, you made Léo a hostage, bro?
You're barbaric!

216
00:15:40,812 --> 00:15:42,854
You piece of shit, that's demented!
How could you?

217
00:15:42,937 --> 00:15:45,021
[angrily] You're damn stupid, King!

218
00:15:45,104 --> 00:15:46,979
You fucking asshole!

219
00:15:47,062 --> 00:15:49,396
We could've sorted this whole thing out.

220
00:15:51,062 --> 00:15:52,979
And kept the kids safe for good.

221
00:15:54,271 --> 00:15:57,521
But, no, you gotta
fuck it all up if you can.

222
00:15:57,604 --> 00:15:59,646
What did our family get out of it?
Tell me!

223
00:15:59,729 --> 00:16:03,062
Do you even care about our family, huh?
You gave them Léo!

224
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:05,604
Only a fucking asshole
would do that kind of shit.

225
00:16:07,937 --> 00:16:11,687
Imagine what Mom would say if you told her
that you gave Léo as a hostage!

226
00:16:12,562 --> 00:16:14,812
And you ask me to fucking disappear?

227
00:16:15,396 --> 00:16:17,271
To repair your shitty mistakes?

228
00:16:18,271 --> 00:16:21,146
It's your problem, Kylian, understand?

229
00:16:21,229 --> 00:16:23,104
You sort this out.

230
00:16:23,896 --> 00:16:25,062
I'm not going anywhere.

231
00:16:36,812 --> 00:16:38,229
[sighs]

232
00:16:49,021 --> 00:16:50,021
[door unlocks]

233
00:16:53,771 --> 00:16:56,854
- Were you careful like I told you?
- Yeah, I didn't see anyone.

234
00:17:03,771 --> 00:17:05,521
What the hell happened to you?

235
00:17:05,604 --> 00:17:06,604
Nothing.

236
00:17:07,187 --> 00:17:08,562
How's that nothing?

237
00:17:10,604 --> 00:17:12,604
[dark music playing]

238
00:17:14,812 --> 00:17:15,854
Margot.

239
00:17:19,729 --> 00:17:20,979
They showed up.

240
00:17:22,062 --> 00:17:24,271
They want me
to tell them when you're here.

241
00:17:24,771 --> 00:17:25,771
SherKhan's men?

242
00:17:27,562 --> 00:17:28,562
Yeah.

243
00:17:29,187 --> 00:17:30,187
Damn.

244
00:17:30,687 --> 00:17:32,146
It's becoming serious.

245
00:17:36,354 --> 00:17:37,354
Truly.

246
00:17:41,354 --> 00:17:42,354
I'll leave.

247
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:44,896
Leave to where?

248
00:17:44,979 --> 00:17:46,937
I've gotta sell those fast.

249
00:17:47,437 --> 00:17:48,521
You got a plan?

250
00:17:49,562 --> 00:17:52,896
Shove them up your own ass
and board a plane yourself. [laughs]

251
00:17:53,729 --> 00:17:55,062
Yeah, you're right.

252
00:17:56,604 --> 00:17:59,021
I'll find a way. I'm resourceful.

253
00:17:59,104 --> 00:18:00,104
I'm the King, right?

254
00:18:01,312 --> 00:18:02,646
Undeniably.

255
00:18:09,687 --> 00:18:10,521
Yeah.

256
00:18:19,437 --> 00:18:20,604
[banging on door]

257
00:18:24,646 --> 00:18:25,896
What do you want?

258
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:26,979
Visitor.

259
00:18:35,562 --> 00:18:36,771
[snaps fingers]

260
00:18:54,187 --> 00:18:58,896
We've all received this.
Fatso, Peace, my brother, and me.

261
00:19:04,271 --> 00:19:06,479
UNION OF DOCKWORKERS
AND DOCKS OF MARTINIQUE

262
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,396
[gentle music playing]

263
00:19:23,854 --> 00:19:27,187
[sighs heavily] I didn't get anything.

264
00:19:27,271 --> 00:19:29,729
He sent it to those who could do the job.

265
00:19:32,937 --> 00:19:34,354
[Kylian sucks teeth]

266
00:19:36,562 --> 00:19:37,896
Jean-Claude.

267
00:19:39,187 --> 00:19:41,062
That son of a bitch.

268
00:19:41,146 --> 00:19:42,437
He put a hit on my brother.

269
00:19:43,354 --> 00:19:44,771
He's one of many.

270
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:49,771
Why are you here?

271
00:19:52,146 --> 00:19:53,771
Because you're alone.

272
00:19:54,437 --> 00:19:57,437
- [gentle music continues]
- [sighs]

273
00:20:19,104 --> 00:20:21,062
[softly] I don't know how to fix this.

274
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,229
[Pearl] Come here.

275
00:20:51,896 --> 00:20:54,062
That's a disgusting thing to do.

276
00:20:55,729 --> 00:20:57,729
Doesn't he have a brother?

277
00:20:59,146 --> 00:21:00,437
Beats me.

278
00:21:01,812 --> 00:21:04,229
It'll change nothing
if we go after his family.

279
00:21:04,312 --> 00:21:06,187
King has too many enemies.

280
00:21:06,729 --> 00:21:08,521
Even Fatso wants him dead.

281
00:21:09,021 --> 00:21:10,396
Even your brother.

282
00:21:10,479 --> 00:21:12,979
[laughs softly] Ludo wouldn't do anything.

283
00:21:13,062 --> 00:21:14,854
If I say "do this," he will.

284
00:21:15,437 --> 00:21:18,437
Make King leave,
that'll calm everyone down.

285
00:21:18,937 --> 00:21:20,354
He's very stubborn.

286
00:21:22,604 --> 00:21:24,062
[Pearl sighs heavily]

287
00:21:27,521 --> 00:21:28,937
Then what would he do?

288
00:21:34,021 --> 00:21:36,437
He was on drugs. He's an idiot.

289
00:21:39,937 --> 00:21:41,354
Where do you get your personality?

290
00:21:42,687 --> 00:21:44,646
My mom, for sure.

291
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:47,229
What would your mother do?

292
00:21:49,562 --> 00:21:50,937
I'm not sure.

293
00:21:52,646 --> 00:21:54,937
She'd make sure
everyone pays for their part.

294
00:21:55,437 --> 00:21:57,937
If someone had forced her
to chop off her arm,

295
00:21:58,021 --> 00:22:00,104
she would definitely take revenge.

296
00:22:01,396 --> 00:22:03,604
She'd chop off both of theirs.

297
00:22:06,896 --> 00:22:07,937
[doorbell rings]

298
00:22:16,396 --> 00:22:18,979
- [Chloé] What's this about now?
- I've gotta speak to Marv.

299
00:22:19,562 --> 00:22:21,021
Didn't bring the whole crew?

300
00:22:22,604 --> 00:22:23,729
Outside.

301
00:22:23,812 --> 00:22:27,104
[angrily] Hey, Kylian!
If you got something to say, say it here.

302
00:22:27,187 --> 00:22:28,771
- I'll be back.
- Marvin!

303
00:22:28,854 --> 00:22:29,937
I'll be back.

304
00:22:32,521 --> 00:22:33,396
[sucks teeth]

305
00:22:40,854 --> 00:22:42,562
Not cool to come here, brother.

306
00:22:43,062 --> 00:22:45,812
- This will blow up in my face.
- They're bailing on me.

307
00:22:52,146 --> 00:22:53,479
Because of King?

308
00:22:54,229 --> 00:22:55,396
They're bailing on me.

309
00:23:08,312 --> 00:23:10,312
[indistinct muted chatter]

310
00:23:13,437 --> 00:23:15,812
[man] We gotta be more careful
about who we let in here.

311
00:23:15,896 --> 00:23:18,729
[woman] Do you have my money?
I lent you 50 euros last week!

312
00:23:18,812 --> 00:23:20,604
You need to give me my share!

313
00:23:20,687 --> 00:23:23,354
I'm running low on cash
and need to buy food.

314
00:23:23,437 --> 00:23:24,771
Are you listening to me?

315
00:23:24,854 --> 00:23:26,729
- You need to give me my money!
- [Marvin] Yuck!

316
00:23:26,812 --> 00:23:31,479
Stop being such a deadbeat husband
and give me what you owe me and the kids!

317
00:23:31,562 --> 00:23:33,854
Are you listening to me? Look at me!

318
00:23:33,937 --> 00:23:36,104
Look at me, you piece of shit!

319
00:23:36,187 --> 00:23:40,062
I know you've been using my money
for drugs and gambling with your boys.

320
00:23:40,146 --> 00:23:41,437
Stop being a dick!

321
00:23:41,521 --> 00:23:44,729
Look at me and pay up,
you spineless manchild!

322
00:23:44,812 --> 00:23:47,146
- [lighter flicks]
- [woman humming indistinctly]

323
00:23:47,229 --> 00:23:49,979
[woman] You won't get away with this,
you piece of shit!

324
00:23:56,937 --> 00:23:59,229
- [Nat] It's not me.
- What you talkin' about?

325
00:24:01,187 --> 00:24:02,646
What are you doin'?

326
00:24:02,729 --> 00:24:03,937
What are you doin'?

327
00:24:04,729 --> 00:24:06,229
I'm keeping watch.

328
00:24:08,396 --> 00:24:09,396
For what?

329
00:24:10,396 --> 00:24:11,771
My little family.

330
00:24:12,521 --> 00:24:15,187
Here, this is my house.
What… What are you doing here?

331
00:24:16,062 --> 00:24:18,062
Did you bring my ring like I asked?

332
00:24:18,146 --> 00:24:19,646
[bag unzips]

333
00:24:20,562 --> 00:24:22,812
We have a job we need you for, Nathanaël.

334
00:24:23,437 --> 00:24:25,854
You'll get twice as much when it's done.

335
00:24:29,729 --> 00:24:32,312
You've never needed me
for anything before.

336
00:24:33,562 --> 00:24:35,062
Okay, but now we do.

337
00:24:45,229 --> 00:24:46,687
That's it, Marvin.

338
00:24:49,021 --> 00:24:51,146
You've found yourself in shit too.

339
00:24:53,812 --> 00:24:56,146
We all end up in it. Relax.

340
00:24:56,937 --> 00:24:59,271
We'll be reunited… as a family.

341
00:24:59,354 --> 00:25:00,687
Obviously.

342
00:25:02,187 --> 00:25:03,187
And here…

343
00:25:03,687 --> 00:25:05,396
will be a home for both of us.

344
00:25:05,479 --> 00:25:07,437
- [laughs]
- Want to help us or not, man?

345
00:25:13,271 --> 00:25:15,812
[darkly intriguing music playing]

346
00:25:24,687 --> 00:25:25,854
[keypad beeping]

347
00:25:28,937 --> 00:25:29,979
[Kylian] Wait here.

348
00:25:39,812 --> 00:25:42,521
[darkly intriguing music continues]

349
00:25:52,187 --> 00:25:53,187
Milord.

350
00:25:54,937 --> 00:25:56,229
What are you doin'?

351
00:25:57,354 --> 00:25:59,187
I'm making sure everything's okay.

352
00:25:59,271 --> 00:26:00,771
I'm taking over, you can go.

353
00:26:02,937 --> 00:26:05,812
Okay, but the plan was for me to be here.
So I'm staying.

354
00:26:07,021 --> 00:26:09,271
It's all right, I told you to move along.

355
00:26:13,979 --> 00:26:16,979
- Okay.
- [darkly intriguing music continues]

356
00:26:30,854 --> 00:26:32,187
Looking for this, buddy?

357
00:26:33,354 --> 00:26:34,354
Get in.

358
00:26:35,729 --> 00:26:37,521
Get a move on, my man!

359
00:26:41,937 --> 00:26:42,937
Now keep still!

360
00:26:43,646 --> 00:26:45,021
- Keep still, man!
- Calm down, bro.

361
00:26:45,104 --> 00:26:46,729
- Calm down, okay?
- Shut up or I'll blow!

362
00:26:47,312 --> 00:26:50,812
- Fuck, I'm sitting! I'm--
- Give me the phone! The phone, give me it!

363
00:27:13,229 --> 00:27:15,604
- Oh hell yeah, brother!
- [tapping loudly]

364
00:27:15,687 --> 00:27:18,562
- We showed them!
- Stop it, Nat! Please, Nat.

365
00:27:21,104 --> 00:27:22,354
And the cash?

366
00:27:24,271 --> 00:27:26,479
The cash! Come on, guys! [clapping]

367
00:27:32,979 --> 00:27:34,479
[softly] That's my ring.

368
00:27:37,771 --> 00:27:39,979
The bougainvillea,
that's your plant, yeah?

369
00:27:42,187 --> 00:27:45,104
Take it, bro.
It isn't Frodo's Ring of Power.

370
00:27:52,854 --> 00:27:55,854
[uplifting music playing]

371
00:28:10,979 --> 00:28:12,354
Thank you. [sniffles]

372
00:28:15,062 --> 00:28:16,979
Seriously, brother.

373
00:28:20,729 --> 00:28:23,729
[uplifting music continues]

374
00:28:26,354 --> 00:28:28,687
- You've always been a Lafleur, Nat.
- [sniffles]

375
00:28:30,854 --> 00:28:32,312
We never forgot.

376
00:28:42,312 --> 00:28:44,479
[uplifting music continues]

377
00:28:49,479 --> 00:28:52,812
Stop harassing Annabelle
and coming unannounced, all right?

378
00:29:01,354 --> 00:29:04,354
[uplifting music continues]

379
00:29:06,521 --> 00:29:08,021
Okay, family.

380
00:29:08,104 --> 00:29:09,229
Okay, my brothers.

381
00:29:09,312 --> 00:29:10,604
Respect, respect.

382
00:29:13,687 --> 00:29:16,312
[music fading]

383
00:29:21,312 --> 00:29:22,687
[Fatso] We all got one.

384
00:29:23,729 --> 00:29:25,896
Someone put a hit on Kingsley Lafleur.

385
00:29:36,104 --> 00:29:37,562
The police are watching you.

386
00:29:37,646 --> 00:29:40,187
They're watching us too, but…

387
00:29:40,271 --> 00:29:44,354
but if you want to try,
we can fill you in on where he goes daily…

388
00:29:44,437 --> 00:29:45,521
and when he does.

389
00:29:46,854 --> 00:29:48,354
Who's he to you guys?

390
00:29:48,437 --> 00:29:50,771
Y'all saved his ass once before.

391
00:29:50,854 --> 00:29:52,937
Not by me. That was Milord.

392
00:29:53,021 --> 00:29:54,687
Milord isn't with y'all?

393
00:29:55,187 --> 00:29:57,229
Milord caused a fucking mess
and screwed us.

394
00:29:57,312 --> 00:29:58,479
It's over.

395
00:29:59,354 --> 00:30:00,479
We…

396
00:30:00,562 --> 00:30:02,021
could be with you guys.

397
00:30:02,604 --> 00:30:03,479
Us?

398
00:30:05,562 --> 00:30:07,646
Y'all managing after SherKhan's death?

399
00:30:13,021 --> 00:30:15,937
Do you have his connections…
to get supplies?

400
00:30:17,437 --> 00:30:18,646
To export?

401
00:30:19,979 --> 00:30:22,021
Do you still have Croquet's boats?

402
00:30:22,979 --> 00:30:24,437
[sighs]

403
00:30:25,896 --> 00:30:29,312
- What do you propose, then?
- We rebuild the business.

404
00:30:29,937 --> 00:30:32,854
It's all upside. We've got all we need.

405
00:30:34,562 --> 00:30:35,687
Who is that?

406
00:30:40,146 --> 00:30:42,354
He's a hitman. I've seen him around.

407
00:30:42,896 --> 00:30:46,312
[Fatso] Take a seat.
He won't do anything with the cops here.

408
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:57,562
[rooster crows in distance]

409
00:31:09,187 --> 00:31:11,354
- [Kylian on speaker] Can they hear me?
- Yes.

410
00:31:13,021 --> 00:31:14,437
Well, Alexy…

411
00:31:15,229 --> 00:31:16,604
I heard rumors.

412
00:31:17,146 --> 00:31:18,771
You've all received envelopes.

413
00:31:19,354 --> 00:31:20,896
I see you've made new friends.

414
00:31:31,312 --> 00:31:32,896
Where you holdin' our stuff?

415
00:31:32,979 --> 00:31:34,646
Your stuff is safe here.

416
00:31:36,146 --> 00:31:37,604
Is that Milord?

417
00:31:38,479 --> 00:31:40,312
[Fatso] Shit's really gonna go down.

418
00:31:40,396 --> 00:31:43,312
[Kylian] Alexy,
if anything happens to King…

419
00:31:43,396 --> 00:31:47,771
anything at all, even a cold,
you can forget about your share.

420
00:31:47,854 --> 00:31:51,312
And if I find out you helped,
each of you will get shot.

421
00:31:52,771 --> 00:31:55,937
And you two there, SherKhan's lackeys.

422
00:31:56,437 --> 00:31:58,646
Go after my family
and I'll go after yours.

423
00:31:58,729 --> 00:31:59,604
All right?

424
00:32:00,104 --> 00:32:04,021
Brothers, sisters, cousins,
kids, adults, I won't discriminate.

425
00:32:05,896 --> 00:32:08,354
Don't get started.
You don't know how I'll end it.

426
00:32:09,437 --> 00:32:11,312
I hope I've made myself clear.

427
00:32:16,104 --> 00:32:18,104
There's a spider under the table.

428
00:32:20,854 --> 00:32:21,854
Oh fuck!

429
00:32:31,646 --> 00:32:33,646
[rooster crows in distance]

430
00:32:38,937 --> 00:32:40,687
[Kylian] Could it go to Trinidad?

431
00:32:40,771 --> 00:32:42,896
I've been all over with it, bro.

432
00:32:44,729 --> 00:32:46,521
- How much?
- 5%.

433
00:32:47,354 --> 00:32:48,646
Five percent of what?

434
00:32:49,396 --> 00:32:51,021
The stuff you've hidden away.

435
00:32:52,771 --> 00:32:55,146
- [sighs]
- Pretty cheap to save your brother.

436
00:32:57,312 --> 00:33:00,312
[darkly intriguing music playing]

437
00:33:34,687 --> 00:33:35,771
[Kingsley whistles]

438
00:33:38,896 --> 00:33:39,937
[whistles]

439
00:34:04,521 --> 00:34:05,604
Are you okay?

440
00:34:06,312 --> 00:34:09,562
All good here.
[laughs] You wanted to tell me something?

441
00:34:12,687 --> 00:34:14,896
- Kylian said that you have to leave.
- [sighs]

442
00:34:14,979 --> 00:34:18,854
- Are you on an undercover mission?
- He said that I could make you understand.

443
00:34:20,271 --> 00:34:22,687
- Did he tell you about Léo?
- No.

444
00:34:22,771 --> 00:34:25,562
- Why?
- [chuckles] Yeah, right. Forget about it.

445
00:34:26,437 --> 00:34:27,521
Go, please!

446
00:34:28,021 --> 00:34:29,479
I'm afraid they'll hurt you.

447
00:34:32,896 --> 00:34:35,146
There's a boat waiting for you
in the Génipa mangrove.

448
00:34:35,229 --> 00:34:37,771
You'll go to Trinidad
where a contact will help you.

449
00:34:38,646 --> 00:34:41,979
That scumbag fucker planned for all this.
He'd love to see me out of the way.

450
00:34:42,062 --> 00:34:43,812
No, he wants to save you, King!

451
00:34:43,896 --> 00:34:45,687
All of us want you safe!

452
00:34:46,396 --> 00:34:47,812
You think you don't matter to us?

453
00:34:51,437 --> 00:34:52,771
And the kids?

454
00:34:54,271 --> 00:34:56,229
Imagine their pain if you're gone.

455
00:35:04,604 --> 00:35:05,937
To get settled.

456
00:35:11,229 --> 00:35:14,021
Fuck, this really blows.

457
00:35:35,229 --> 00:35:37,021
[Kingsley inhales sharply]

458
00:35:38,437 --> 00:35:41,437
["EDEN" by Mob BoBoy playing]

459
00:35:52,354 --> 00:35:55,354
- ["EDEN" continues playing]
- [inaudible]

460
00:36:10,646 --> 00:36:13,146
- Didier?
- ["EDEN" continues playing]

461
00:36:24,354 --> 00:36:27,062
[Didier] Here's what you'll tell
the person who sent you here.

462
00:36:27,146 --> 00:36:29,271
You go tell them to fuck themselves.

463
00:36:29,354 --> 00:36:32,312
If they want my help,
they should just come to me.

464
00:36:32,854 --> 00:36:35,354
- So I came to you myself.
- [music stops]

465
00:36:35,437 --> 00:36:36,771
How much you got?

466
00:36:36,854 --> 00:36:37,979
One ton.

467
00:36:39,771 --> 00:36:45,354
DUCOS PENITENTIARY

468
00:36:48,854 --> 00:36:50,562
[door buzzing]

469
00:37:08,104 --> 00:37:10,937
It seems that you have information
about the death of SherKhan?

470
00:37:11,021 --> 00:37:12,021
Possibly.

471
00:37:12,771 --> 00:37:14,062
Talk.

472
00:37:14,729 --> 00:37:18,354
[sputtering] Yo, well, talk? Talk…
This isn't for free, all right, bro?

473
00:37:19,187 --> 00:37:20,812
If I talk, I can't stay here.

474
00:37:20,896 --> 00:37:22,604
I'd be a walking corpse.

475
00:37:23,604 --> 00:37:25,437
Sharing here wouldn't be safe.

476
00:37:26,146 --> 00:37:28,146
I want to get out with an ankle monitor.

477
00:37:29,562 --> 00:37:33,229
- That's above my rank.
- Bring me a person with the rank.

478
00:37:35,812 --> 00:37:37,229
Kingsley Lafleur, is he your son?

479
00:37:40,562 --> 00:37:41,562
No.

480
00:37:41,646 --> 00:37:44,396
My son is Kylian Lafleur.

481
00:37:45,146 --> 00:37:47,146
[ominous music playing]

482
00:37:49,021 --> 00:37:50,437
Lafleur!

483
00:38:01,312 --> 00:38:02,479
Let's go.

484
00:38:03,396 --> 00:38:05,146
- Why?
- Move it.

485
00:38:05,229 --> 00:38:07,229
[suspenseful music playing]

486
00:38:16,729 --> 00:38:17,729
Where are we going?

487
00:38:17,812 --> 00:38:19,396
To the station.

488
00:38:25,021 --> 00:38:27,021
[suspenseful music continues]

489
00:38:50,854 --> 00:38:52,812
[suspenseful music continues]

490
00:39:07,229 --> 00:39:08,396
Hungry?

491
00:39:13,229 --> 00:39:15,396
[sings softly]
♪ Well, have a seat, Milord ♪

492
00:39:15,479 --> 00:39:18,354
♪ Come sit down at my table ♪

493
00:39:18,937 --> 00:39:22,187
♪ It's very cold, freezing outside ♪

494
00:39:22,271 --> 00:39:23,437
♪ Here, it's comfortable ♪

495
00:39:26,021 --> 00:39:27,271
Not familiar with Édith Piaf?

496
00:39:41,521 --> 00:39:44,021
You should know
King dropped by here the other day.

497
00:39:44,729 --> 00:39:46,812
I lent him a pile of money.

498
00:39:48,687 --> 00:39:51,896
I predict, with the situation,
he won't be able to repay me.

499
00:39:53,646 --> 00:39:54,646
And?

500
00:39:56,062 --> 00:39:57,854
Do you know what collateral is?

501
00:40:01,937 --> 00:40:03,437
I see you do.

502
00:40:04,562 --> 00:40:09,104
With the repayment on the principal,
a fee of 15% on your family profits.

503
00:40:10,187 --> 00:40:11,896
That's what collateral is.

504
00:40:14,646 --> 00:40:16,812
The profits of the Lafleur family?

505
00:40:17,396 --> 00:40:19,437
Flourishing, by your father's testimony.

506
00:40:23,146 --> 00:40:24,354
My father?

507
00:40:25,229 --> 00:40:27,646
He seems very family-oriented.

508
00:40:31,729 --> 00:40:33,437
He's just talking bullshit.

509
00:40:34,229 --> 00:40:37,771
I urged my policemen buddies
to abstain from verifying, but…

510
00:40:38,812 --> 00:40:40,604
they might at any moment.

511
00:40:41,812 --> 00:40:44,437
Your business affairs,
do they investigate those too?

512
00:40:46,312 --> 00:40:48,604
No one's bold enough to investigate.

513
00:40:57,437 --> 00:40:59,187
We could make a bargain then.

514
00:41:01,979 --> 00:41:04,021
Maybe you could do something
to help my brother.

515
00:41:04,604 --> 00:41:05,604
What?

516
00:41:06,146 --> 00:41:09,437
Just protect him
so he can remain on the island.

517
00:41:09,937 --> 00:41:11,312
From whom?

518
00:41:12,521 --> 00:41:13,812
Everybody.

519
00:41:19,229 --> 00:41:20,937
He's a burden, your brother.

520
00:41:23,521 --> 00:41:24,687
No.

521
00:41:24,771 --> 00:41:26,771
I don't want anything to do with him.

522
00:41:29,354 --> 00:41:31,396
He's bound to fuck things up.

523
00:41:37,146 --> 00:41:39,812
I prefer working with folks
that don't diss my family.

524
00:41:40,854 --> 00:41:43,896
I could bring
lots of problems to your family.

525
00:41:46,062 --> 00:41:48,437
I could bring lots
of unwanted problems to yours too.

526
00:41:51,979 --> 00:41:53,062
You know that.

527
00:41:55,854 --> 00:41:58,854
[dark music building]

528
00:42:06,729 --> 00:42:08,271
VIDEO MESSAGE

529
00:42:13,854 --> 00:42:16,854
[dark music continues]

530
00:42:25,479 --> 00:42:27,937
- [woman in Spanish] Cristina?
- Yes, Mom?

531
00:42:28,021 --> 00:42:31,104
[woman] Come over here, sweetheart.
It's time.

532
00:42:38,062 --> 00:42:39,396
[man whistles on video]

533
00:42:43,687 --> 00:42:45,271
Are you filming?

534
00:42:48,812 --> 00:42:50,396
[Léo on video] Are you filming?

535
00:42:54,312 --> 00:42:55,312
[gun fires]

536
00:42:55,396 --> 00:42:56,771
[in English] No!

537
00:42:58,021 --> 00:43:00,396
- No!
- [somber music playing]

538
00:43:01,396 --> 00:43:02,437
[exclaims]

539
00:43:03,062 --> 00:43:04,646
[whimpers] Oh, fuck!

540
00:43:09,146 --> 00:43:11,146
[sobbing]

541
00:43:14,771 --> 00:43:18,062
[sobbing] Léo! Oh God…

542
00:43:21,854 --> 00:43:24,437
[phone ringing]

543
00:43:27,604 --> 00:43:29,562
- [ringing continues]
- [crying]

544
00:43:33,854 --> 00:43:36,354
[ringing continues]

545
00:43:47,437 --> 00:43:48,437
Léo?

546
00:43:48,937 --> 00:43:50,479
Yeah, hey, brother.

547
00:43:50,562 --> 00:43:53,146
I've got something to share.
You see this thing?

548
00:43:53,229 --> 00:43:55,104
Well, I got shot straight in the head.

549
00:43:55,187 --> 00:43:56,437
Boom!

550
00:43:56,521 --> 00:44:00,104
But, relax, it was a blank,
not a real bullet, bro.

551
00:44:00,187 --> 00:44:01,687
It hurt like hell, though.

552
00:44:01,771 --> 00:44:04,646
But it was to toughen me up, you know?
So I can be fierce.

553
00:44:06,437 --> 00:44:08,479
- What's wrong, are you crying?
- No.

554
00:44:08,562 --> 00:44:09,604
You all right?

555
00:44:09,687 --> 00:44:12,021
Oh! They asked me to tell you something.

556
00:44:12,104 --> 00:44:16,396
[in Spanish] "The only guarantee…
is death."

557
00:44:16,479 --> 00:44:18,104
[in English] Do you understand?

558
00:44:18,187 --> 00:44:20,354
Is there someone there? Put him on.

559
00:44:22,146 --> 00:44:25,229
[in Spanish] He wants to talk to you.

560
00:44:26,896 --> 00:44:27,729
CALL ENDED

561
00:44:30,562 --> 00:44:31,687
[phone clatters]

562
00:44:41,229 --> 00:44:43,104
[Lily] Kylian? Are you okay?

563
00:44:43,771 --> 00:44:45,229
What's happening?

564
00:44:47,396 --> 00:44:48,437
Kylian!

565
00:44:49,312 --> 00:44:50,312
What's wrong?

566
00:44:50,812 --> 00:44:52,271
I'm in deep shit.

567
00:44:53,562 --> 00:44:55,646
I'm visiting my uncle, maybe he can help.

568
00:44:56,146 --> 00:44:57,479
No, he can't.

569
00:44:57,562 --> 00:44:59,896
I just spoke with Croquet.
It's impossible.

570
00:44:59,979 --> 00:45:01,271
You were with him?

571
00:45:04,354 --> 00:45:05,979
Tell me what's happening.

572
00:45:06,062 --> 00:45:09,687
I'm being forced to pick
and chop either my left or my right arm.

573
00:45:10,562 --> 00:45:12,812
If I can't choose, I'll lose both of 'em.

574
00:45:15,021 --> 00:45:17,937
[pensive music playing]

575
00:45:22,062 --> 00:45:23,562
This isn't your world.

576
00:45:24,354 --> 00:45:25,812
I want to stay with you.

577
00:45:28,104 --> 00:45:29,104
No.

578
00:45:30,521 --> 00:45:31,937
I'll call you, all right?

579
00:45:32,729 --> 00:45:34,104
I want to help you.

580
00:45:34,979 --> 00:45:36,646
It's beyond both of us.

581
00:45:39,104 --> 00:45:41,562
Call me, please? Promise?

582
00:45:42,979 --> 00:45:45,979
- Yeah, promise.
- [pensive music continues]

583
00:46:01,854 --> 00:46:05,146
[pensive music building]

584
00:46:11,396 --> 00:46:12,896
- [music fades]
- [laughing]

585
00:46:13,771 --> 00:46:16,687
- Tag, you're it!
- Ahh! Cannonball!

586
00:46:17,604 --> 00:46:19,729
[indistinct chatter]

587
00:46:19,812 --> 00:46:21,604
- [kid 1] Your turn!
- [kid 2] It's your turn!

588
00:46:21,687 --> 00:46:23,687
[chatter continues]

589
00:46:27,771 --> 00:46:30,562
- [kid] Hey!
- [chatter and laughter]

590
00:46:36,437 --> 00:46:37,896
[kid] Let's do it again!

591
00:46:39,312 --> 00:46:43,396
That's so sweet.
Right after the message. Ambre, look.

592
00:46:50,104 --> 00:46:51,229
[Annabelle] What?

593
00:46:51,312 --> 00:46:52,771
Seriously, Belle?

594
00:46:53,604 --> 00:46:56,062
You're being a bunch of clowns
with this behavior.

595
00:46:56,146 --> 00:46:57,146
[sucks teeth]

596
00:46:58,771 --> 00:47:00,187
Don't be like that.

597
00:47:00,271 --> 00:47:02,604
- Ridiculous.
- Let go just a bit, Ambre.

598
00:47:03,604 --> 00:47:05,854
Okay, you're mad, we get it.

599
00:47:05,937 --> 00:47:08,562
But, look, we're all together.
That's great, no?

600
00:47:10,604 --> 00:47:11,604
Together?

601
00:47:14,854 --> 00:47:17,479
Do you realize
we're all now complicit in this?

602
00:47:18,646 --> 00:47:20,562
If they get busted, we'll get busted too.

603
00:47:21,604 --> 00:47:23,729
True, so we should be helping each other.

604
00:47:29,771 --> 00:47:30,854
Who are you?

605
00:47:34,271 --> 00:47:35,479
I am your brother.

606
00:47:35,562 --> 00:47:38,479
- [Thaïs] Who's your daddy?
- Daddy Lafleur.

607
00:47:40,312 --> 00:47:41,354
The rings.

608
00:47:41,937 --> 00:47:43,729
I came up with the idea.

609
00:47:43,812 --> 00:47:45,896
Don't worry, you'll get yours someday.

610
00:47:46,396 --> 00:47:49,771
- We have to get King out before nightfall.
- I have it under control.

611
00:47:53,687 --> 00:47:55,271
Sorry, but I can't.

612
00:47:56,229 --> 00:47:58,062
I'm trying, but I can't.

613
00:47:59,104 --> 00:48:00,687
It's too hard for me.

614
00:48:02,687 --> 00:48:03,729
[Thaïs] King!

615
00:48:04,562 --> 00:48:06,646
- [Nolan] King!
- [Thaïs] Kingsley!

616
00:48:08,354 --> 00:48:10,437
- Hi, there, alligators!
- Are you coming to swim?

617
00:48:10,521 --> 00:48:11,854
Oh no! You guys are all wet!

618
00:48:13,562 --> 00:48:14,979
[sighs heavily]

619
00:48:19,187 --> 00:48:22,229
- [Mathis] Let's go, let's go, let's go!
- Okay, okay, give me a second.

620
00:48:22,312 --> 00:48:23,312
Yeah, all right.

621
00:48:23,396 --> 00:48:25,437
[kids laughing]

622
00:48:25,521 --> 00:48:28,146
- [Mathis] Come on, come on, come on!
- [kids laughing]

623
00:48:28,229 --> 00:48:30,896
- [Thaïs] Come on, hurry up!
- [Kingsley exclaiming]

624
00:48:32,979 --> 00:48:34,854
Nobody followed me, don't worry.

625
00:48:34,937 --> 00:48:37,062
[Mathis] There's so many fish today.

626
00:48:39,146 --> 00:48:41,479
- Move out of my way, Thaïs.
- Come on, girls!

627
00:48:43,021 --> 00:48:44,521
Cleansing bath time, guys.

628
00:48:44,604 --> 00:48:47,896
- That's only for New Years.
- And did you cleanse on New Years or not?

629
00:48:49,396 --> 00:48:51,104
- Get in the water, Cass.
- [sighs]

630
00:48:51,187 --> 00:48:53,604
Let's wash off the super bad vibes.

631
00:48:54,312 --> 00:48:56,146
But first, it's makeup time.

632
00:48:57,521 --> 00:48:59,521
[kids laughing]

633
00:49:03,979 --> 00:49:05,687
- I'm a ghost.
- Keep still, King.

634
00:49:05,771 --> 00:49:07,771
[laughter continues]

635
00:49:11,146 --> 00:49:12,771
Your turn, Kiki!

636
00:49:12,854 --> 00:49:14,979
Come on,
it's your turn to cleanse yourself.

637
00:49:18,562 --> 00:49:21,562
- [Thaïs] Wait for me!
- [Nat] Whoo! This is dope! Bring it on!

638
00:49:21,646 --> 00:49:23,437
Kick his ass! kick his ass!

639
00:49:23,521 --> 00:49:26,354
- Motherfucker, Léo should have been here.
- [Kylian gasps]

640
00:49:29,562 --> 00:49:30,646
Hey, King.

641
00:49:31,521 --> 00:49:32,854
King!

642
00:49:33,604 --> 00:49:34,687
One down.

643
00:49:34,771 --> 00:49:36,687
Free from all bad curses!

644
00:49:38,521 --> 00:49:41,229
- You let this happen for real?
- We had no choice, King.

645
00:49:41,312 --> 00:49:43,854
- You had no choice? No choice?
- We had no choice.

646
00:49:45,604 --> 00:49:47,062
Come on, it's cleansing time!

647
00:49:49,896 --> 00:49:52,104
[Annabelle laughing] It's King's turn!

648
00:49:53,229 --> 00:49:55,229
No, no, no! Hey! Hey! Get away!

649
00:49:55,312 --> 00:49:56,854
[Cassandra] Your turn, King!

650
00:49:56,937 --> 00:49:59,521
Kick his ass! Kick his ass! Kick his ass!
[imitates gun firing]

651
00:49:59,604 --> 00:50:00,771
[Kingsley] No more! No more!

652
00:50:00,854 --> 00:50:02,604
- [Cassandra] King!
- [Annabelle laughing]

653
00:50:03,646 --> 00:50:04,854
[laughing] Stop!

654
00:50:08,521 --> 00:50:10,729
[Annabelle yelps and laughs]

655
00:50:10,812 --> 00:50:12,937
[Thaïs laughing] Ahh! This is so much fun!

656
00:50:13,021 --> 00:50:15,146
[Nolan laughing] Stay still!

657
00:50:16,812 --> 00:50:19,229
- [Cassandra] Take some chips.
- [Thaïs] Thank you.

658
00:50:20,354 --> 00:50:21,812
[Cassandra] Do you want more?

659
00:50:22,562 --> 00:50:24,271
[Thaïs] Yes, please, can I have more?

660
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:26,646
- [Annabelle] Me too.
- [Marvin] Me three. Thanks, Cass.

661
00:50:26,729 --> 00:50:29,479
[Cassandra] No problem.
There's enough for everyone.

662
00:50:33,271 --> 00:50:35,937
- [sighs heavily]
- [family chatting indistinctly]

663
00:50:36,021 --> 00:50:37,229
You were right.

664
00:50:40,229 --> 00:50:42,187
The streets are really shitty.

665
00:50:44,146 --> 00:50:45,979
You were right from the start.

666
00:50:47,146 --> 00:50:48,187
I'm sorry.

667
00:50:49,604 --> 00:50:51,687
True, but now that's useless.

668
00:50:51,771 --> 00:50:54,187
Yeah, I know. Even so.

669
00:50:58,187 --> 00:51:00,104
I heard your last rap song.

670
00:51:02,021 --> 00:51:07,396
[humming tune]

671
00:51:09,229 --> 00:51:10,396
You're great at it.

672
00:51:16,812 --> 00:51:18,271
What are you planning to do?

673
00:51:21,104 --> 00:51:22,312
I'll be leaving.

674
00:51:23,979 --> 00:51:24,979
To where?

675
00:51:26,229 --> 00:51:27,271
Far away.

676
00:51:28,521 --> 00:51:30,229
I've gotta stop fuckin' up.

677
00:51:33,479 --> 00:51:35,812
I started working on a new song, you know.

678
00:51:36,854 --> 00:51:38,271
Can you play it?

679
00:51:40,354 --> 00:51:43,521
- [Nolan] Hurry up, Thaïs!
- [Mathis] Keep up with us, Thaïs, okay?

680
00:51:54,229 --> 00:51:57,437
[Annabelle] I have the keys.
I'll open the door, just wait.

681
00:51:58,979 --> 00:52:00,062
Hold on!

682
00:52:00,937 --> 00:52:03,937
[bittersweet music playing]

683
00:52:04,021 --> 00:52:05,104
[Annabelle] Give me that.

684
00:52:06,771 --> 00:52:08,521
[Marvin] Thaïs. Pants.

685
00:52:08,604 --> 00:52:10,437
[Annabelle] Careful with your heads.

686
00:52:10,937 --> 00:52:14,437
- [bittersweet music continues]
- [Annabelle] Don't put it like that.

687
00:52:16,479 --> 00:52:17,896
Who will I meet at the port?

688
00:52:18,479 --> 00:52:20,021
Someone trustworthy.

689
00:52:28,187 --> 00:52:29,937
Could you sell these for me?

690
00:52:30,021 --> 00:52:31,521
And send me the cash?

691
00:52:32,104 --> 00:52:33,937
I'll have someone send you the rest.

692
00:52:38,687 --> 00:52:40,604
[Marvin] Give me the other bag, Nolan.

693
00:52:40,687 --> 00:52:42,854
- [Kingsley sighs]
- [Marvin] Go sit down.

694
00:52:42,937 --> 00:52:44,896
[Annabelle] Give me that bag.

695
00:52:46,604 --> 00:52:49,271
I won't be back
by the time they're able to come home.

696
00:52:50,896 --> 00:52:52,396
They'll be safe if I leave?

697
00:52:52,479 --> 00:52:53,729
Léo as well?

698
00:52:55,937 --> 00:52:56,937
Promise?

699
00:52:57,021 --> 00:52:57,896
Promise.

700
00:53:00,979 --> 00:53:02,354
It'll fix all this, right?

701
00:53:03,646 --> 00:53:04,937
Yeah, it will.

702
00:53:05,937 --> 00:53:08,937
[bittersweet music continues]

703
00:53:14,146 --> 00:53:15,479
It's all your fault.

704
00:53:17,146 --> 00:53:19,562
But I admit, it's also my fault.

705
00:53:25,437 --> 00:53:27,271
Take care of the kids, Milord.

706
00:53:28,396 --> 00:53:30,396
[bittersweet music building]

707
00:53:38,312 --> 00:53:40,312
[indistinct chatter]

708
00:53:43,271 --> 00:53:45,937
[Nolan] Can we play I Spy
on the ride home?

709
00:53:47,979 --> 00:53:49,187
I'll miss ya!

710
00:53:49,271 --> 00:53:51,271
- See ya later!
- [Kingsley] See you later!

711
00:53:58,646 --> 00:54:01,646
[bittersweet music building]

712
00:54:15,854 --> 00:54:18,854
["La Tête haute" sung by Ambre playing]

713
00:54:48,562 --> 00:54:51,562
["La Tête haute" continues playing]

714
00:55:30,229 --> 00:55:31,562
- [gun fires]
- [music stops]

715
00:55:53,312 --> 00:55:54,437
There's a car coming!

716
00:55:56,687 --> 00:55:57,687
[gun fires]

717
00:56:28,604 --> 00:56:30,604
[car approaching]

718
00:56:31,562 --> 00:56:34,562
["La Tête haute" playing on car stereo]

719
00:56:46,562 --> 00:56:48,562
[kids bickering indistinctly]

720
00:56:50,104 --> 00:56:52,062
[bickering continues]

721
00:57:01,937 --> 00:57:04,937
["La Tête haute" fading into background]

722
00:57:12,396 --> 00:57:15,396
[majestic music playing]

723
00:57:39,396 --> 00:57:42,396
- [sighs heavily]
- [majestic music continues]

724
00:57:52,146 --> 00:57:53,146
[gun cocks]

725
00:57:59,687 --> 00:58:01,354
[JC] Is there space to negotiate?

726
00:58:01,437 --> 00:58:03,604
There was. Not anymore.

727
00:58:04,187 --> 00:58:05,312
[gun fires]

728
00:58:06,229 --> 00:58:08,229
DUCOS PENITENTIARY

729
00:58:09,396 --> 00:58:12,396
[majestic music continues]

730
00:58:18,687 --> 00:58:21,687
[majestic music building]

731
00:58:27,812 --> 00:58:29,354
[crying softly] I'm sorry.

732
00:58:30,437 --> 00:58:31,604
I'm sorry.

733
00:58:35,521 --> 00:58:37,521
[music fading]

734
00:59:05,187 --> 00:59:08,187
[darkly intriguing music playing]

735
00:59:31,187 --> 00:59:34,187
[darkly intriguing music continues]
